<div class="container shadow p-3 mb-5 bg-white rounded">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            <img id="img1" src="https://image.freepik.com/free-photo/doctor-is-sharing-pills-hands-another-doctor_1157-31404.jpg" width="550px" height="400px" style="float:left">
        </div>
        <div class="col">
            <pre>
            <h2 style="font-family:'Gill Sans', 'Gill Sans MT', Calibri, 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif">Donate Meds. 
Change Lives.</h2>
         </pre>
            <p style="color:black " class="text-end">
                We often are left over with surplus medicines. Many a times, we do not consume all the medicines from a bottle or a strip and then are faced with a dilemma as to what to do with them. On the other hand there are several people who are in need of such expensive medicines in the course of their treatment, but cant afford to buy these.

                ShareMeds was brainchild of three young boys: Urjil, Youg and Haard. They understood the dilemma faced by those who had surplus medicines as well as those who are medicine deficit. They devised a technique to bridge the gap —- they would collect surplus and donate to the deficit areas.
            </p>
        </div>
        
    </div>
</div>
<div class="container text-center shadow p-3 mb-5 bg-white rounded">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            <h2>Why Donate?</h2>
            <br />
            <p style="color:black " class="text-start">
                Unused medicines in our health systems and homes can be responsibly collected and distributed to clinics and pharmacies serving patients struggling with medication insecurity. Tons of medicine can be saved. Millions of lives can be changed.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col">
            <img id="img2" src="https://cdn.aarp.net/content/dam/aarp/health/drugs_supplements/2022/11/1140-how-to-donate-drugs.jpg" width="550px" height="400px" style="float:right">
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container text-center ">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            <h3>MEDICATION DONATION GUIDELINES</h3>
            <ul style="text-align:left">
                <li>We accept prescription and cancer medicines that are not expired.</li>
                <li>Bottles must be sealed (if you take the cap off the bottle from the manufacturer, there will be a seal across the top that you have to open in order to get to the medication), the pills in blister packs that you 'push out' and inhalers must be in their foil/plastic packaging.</li>
                <li>We accept good-dated (not expired) drug samples from physicians or pharmaceutical companies.</li>
                <li>We do not accept narcotics.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
